text: Warus Quta (Aymara warusa grey-brown, quta lake, see: Color "grey-brown lake", also spelled Barros Kota) is a lake in the Cordillera Real in the Andes of Bolivia. It is situated in the La Paz Department, Larecaja Province, Sorata Municipality.IGM map 1:50,000 5946-III Comunidad Amaguaya Warus Quta lies south-east of the mountains Wiluyu Janq'u Uma and Yapuchañani and north-east of Uma Jalanta. == References == Category:Lakes of La Paz Department (Bolivia)
title: Warus Quta (Larecaja)
